# Environment shared by every rosadmin unit that reads Solidarity Tech or mirrors
# to Google, referenced by both the web service and the reconcile sweep through
# EnvironmentFile=. One rendered source means the tenant a unit impersonates and
# the roster it reads cannot drift between the two. Rendered per stage from the
# encrypted secrets; systemd reads it as root at unit start, so the file itself
# stays root-only.
#
# Staging's Solidarity Tech source is the in-process mock (loopback only); the
# persona map is the boot roster the admin socket then mutates at runtime.
SOLIDARITY_TECH_MOCK=1
SOLIDARITY_TECH_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8001
SOLIDARITY_TECH_MOCK_PERSONAS=${st_mock_personas}
# This service's share of the Solidarity Tech key's request budget - the key is
# shared with the Discord bot, so the two consumers' shares sum under the limit.
SOLIDARITY_TECH_REQUEST_BUDGET=40
# The Workspace user the DWD service account impersonates.
ROSADMIN_GOOGLE_SUBJECT=${google_dwd_subject}
# Staging carries example-domain member addresses (test personas), so their sync
# skips log quietly rather than as warnings.
ROSADMIN_EXPECT_EXAMPLE_EMAILS=1
